obflags_in.description: Read 2D rather than 3D coordinates if both provided.
Preserve aromaticity present in the SMILES.
obflags_in.further_info: This option should only be used if reading aromatic SMILES generated by the same version of Open Babel. Any other use will lead to undefined behaviour. The advantage of this option is that it avoids aromaticity perception, thus speeding up reading SMILES.

By default, stereochemistry is accepted as given. If you wish to clean up stereochemistry (e.g., by removing tetrahedral stereochemistry where two of the substituents are identical) then specifying this option will reperceive stereocentres.

obflags_in.description: Add InChI string to molecule name.
Add Tanimoto coeff to title in similarity search.
Read UCSF Dock scores saved in comments preceding molecules.
Apply periodic boundary conditions for bonds.

obflags_in.further_info: When filtering an sdf file on title or properties only, avoid lengthy chemical interpretation by using the T or P option together with the copy format.

obflags_in.description: Determine chirality from atom parity flags.
obflags_in.further_info: The default setting for 2D and 3D is to ignore atom parity and work out the chirality based on the bond stereochemistry (2D) or coordinates (3D). For 0D the default is already to determine the chirality from the atom parity.

obflags_in.description: Do not read stereochemistry from 0D MOL files.
obflags_in.further_info: Open Babel supports reading and writing cis/trans and tetrahedral stereochemistry to 0D MOL files. This is an extension to the standard which you can turn off using this option.

obflags_in.description: Wrap atomic coordinates into unit cell box.
Use bonds listed in CIF file from _geom_bond_etc records (overrides option b).
Input file is in DLG (AutoDock docking log) format.

obflags_in.further_info: Alternative to using 'exact' with option s.

obflags_in.description: Overwrite molecule if more than one.
obflags_in.further_info: Calculation with different molecules is present in the output file (last calculation will be preferred).

obflags_in.description: Molecule name follows InChI on same line.

Always specify the valence in the valence field.
obflags_out.further_info: The default behaviour is to specify the valence if it is not consistent with the MDL valence model. So, for CH4 we do not specify it, but we do for CH3. This option may be useful to preserve the correct number of implicit hydrogens if a downstream tool does not correctly implement the MDL valence model (but does honour the valence field).

obargflags_out.further_info: This atom will be used to begin the SMILES string.
The output will be rearranged so that any additional SMILES added to the end will be attached to this atom.
The atom numbers should be specified like 1 2 4 7.
For example, 'yellow' or '#88ff00' ('none' is transparent and leaving blank is black with white bonds). The atom symbol colours work with black and white backgrounds, but may not with other colours.

obargflags_out.description: Set the cell vectors if not present.
Set the length of the boundary box around the molecule.
obargflags_out.further_info: The default is to make a cube around the molecule, adding 50% to the most positive and negative cartesian coordinate.

obargflags_out.description: For each surface, specify the point density (default is 1.0 angstrom^2).

obargflags_out.further_info: If not specified, the default fingerprint (currently FP2) is used.

obargflags_out.description: Indicate the level of the output file: 0 (default), 1 or 2.
Generate Canonical SMILES for a fragment.
obargflags_out.further_info: The atom numbers should be specified like 1 2 4 7.

obargflags_out.description: Image height in characters (default is width/aspect).
Highlight mol if condition is met.
obargflags_out.further_info: The condition can use descriptors and properties. See documentation on --filter option for details. To highlight in a particular colour, follow the condition by a colour.

obargflags_out.description: Use the specified keywords for input.
Indicate the mode for level 2 output files.
obargflags_out.further_info: 0 (default) is for acceleration and 1 for forces.

obargflags_out.description: Fold to specified number of bits, 32, 64, 128, etc.
Maximum number of objects to be output.

obargflags_out.further_info: Ordering should be specified like 4-2-1-3 for a 4-atom molecule. This gives canonical labels 1,2,3,4 to atoms 4,2,1,3 respectively, so that atom 4 will be visited first and the remaining atoms visited in a depth-first manner following the lowest canonical labels.

obargflags_out.description: px Scale to bond length (single mol only).

obargflags_out.further_info: The two options are SPC (default) or SPCE.

obargflags_out.further_info: A comma-separated list of VDW radius multiples.

obargflags_out.description: Scale-factor for VDW radius in angstroms (default is 1.0).

obargflags_out.further_info: Canonicalisation can take a while for symmetrical molecules and so a timeout is used. The default is 5 seconds.

obargflags_out.description: Truncate InChI according to various parameters.
obargflags_out.further_info: /formula (formula only). /connect (formula and connectivity only). /nostereo (ignore E/Z and sp3 stereochemistry). /nosp3 (ignore sp3 stereochemistry). /noEZ (ignore E/Z stereochemistry). /nochg (ignore charge and protonation). /noiso (ignore isotopes). Note that these can be combined (e.g., /nochg/noiso).
